[[BlasTech Industries/Legends|BlasTech Industries]]' '''DL-18 Blaster Pistol''' was an inexpensive [[Blaster/Legends|blaster]] commonly used during the time of the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].

==Description==
The DL-18 Blaster Pistol was manufactured by [[BlasTech Industries/Legends|BlasTech Industries]].<ref name="RASB" /> They weighed one [[Kilogram/Legends|kilogram]],<ref name="AEG" /> and the [[Blaster power pack/Legends|blaster power pack]] carried one hundred shots.<ref name="RPG2" /> The weapon had a range up to one hundred and twenty [[Meter/Legends|meters]].<ref name="RASB2" /> DL-18s cost five hundred [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credits]] to buy,<ref name="RASB" /> and replacement power packs retailed for twenty-five credits.<ref name="RPG2" />

==History==
{{Quote|The DL-18 for my hip, the sleeve gun for surprise, and... yes the lightsaber. Old fashioned, but useful.|[[Mara Jade Skywalker|Mara Jade]]|<ref name="BtEH">''[[Star Wars: Mara Jade – By the Emperor's Hand]]''</ref>}}
[[File:D18pistol.png|thumb|left|300px|The D-18 Liquidator variant of the DL-18 Blaster Pistol]]
For [[Standard decade/Legends|decades]], the DL-18 was one of [[The galaxy/Legends|the galaxy's]] most prevalent blaster pistols. The basic design was the foundation for several of BlasTech's later designs, and the weapon was versatile to be used in multiple situations. The DL-18's chief competition was [[Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc./Legends|Merr-Sonn Munitions, Inc.'s]] [[Model 44 blaster pistol|Model 44]]. The weapons were often modified by their owners.<ref name="AEG" /> Various [[Spacer/Legends|spacers]] used them during the [[Galactic Civil War/Legends|Galactic Civil War]].<ref name="SWG">{{GalaxiesAED}}</ref> The weapon was considered to be practically disposable due to its inexpensive price.<ref name="TOTC">{{SWGTCG|set=Threat of the Conqueror|cardname=DL-18 Blaster Pistol}}</ref>

[[File:Luke-DL18.jpg|thumb|right|300px|Luke Skywalker aims Nizuc Bek's DL-18 at Jabba the Hutt.]]
[[Officer/Legends|Officers]] serving in the [[Alliance to Restore the Republic/Legends|Alliance to Restore the Republic]],<ref name="RASB" /> such as [[Bria Tharen]],<ref name="RD">''[[Rebel Dawn]]''</ref> favored the lighter, sleeker, DL-18s over heavier blaster pistols.<ref name="RASB" /> The Rebel Alliance officer [[Rannd Delckis]] carried the weapon during the [[Bakura Incident]]<ref name="Bakura Sourcebook">''[[The Truce at Bakura Sourcebook]]''</ref> in [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].<ref name="4 ABY">According to ''[[The Truce at Bakura]]'', the [[Battle of Bakura]] occurred shortly after the [[Battle of Endor/Legends|Battle of Endor]], which ''[[The Essential Guide to Warfare]]'' dates to [[4 ABY/Legends|4 ABY]].</ref> The [[Sith Shadows]] also favored the weapon.<ref name="TOTC" /> The weapon was also known as a "[[Mos Eisley/Legends|Mos Eisley]] Special"&mdash;named after the [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooinian]] [[City/Legends|city]]&mdash;due to the fact that it was a common weapon in use amongst the [[Outlaw|criminals]] of the settlement.<ref name="AEG" /> The weapons were common among the [[Security guard/Legends|guards]] working for [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]].<ref name="JP">{{CCG|set=Jabba's Palace Limited|cardname=Mos Eisley Blaster (Dark)}}</ref> The [[Gunslinger/Legends|gunslinger]] [[Longo Two-Guns]] armed himself with twin DL-18s.<ref name="Gunslingers">{{SW|url=news/so-uncivilized-great-gunslingers-in-star-wars-part-1|series=So Uncivilized: Great Gunslingers in Star Wars|text=Part 1|nolive=1}}</ref> After the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]], a DL-18 was awarded by [[Jabba Desilijic Tiure/Legends|Jabba the Hutt's]] [[Supervisor droid/Legends|supervisor droid]] [[EV-9D9/Legends|EV-9D9]] to a spacer who attacked the [[Valarian Depot]] on Tatooine.<ref name="SWG:R">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Legacy|Remodeling|Tatooine}}</ref> Another was awarded by [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Snopel]] to a [[Commando/Legends|commando]] who defeated the [[Mountain Poachers]] on [[Naboo/Legends|Naboo]].<ref name="SWG:CtT">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=class|Commando|Clearing the Trash|Naboo}}</ref> A variant of this weapon was the D-18 Liquidator, which [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Joth]] of the [[Corellian Security Force]] once offered a spacer as a reward for successfully shutting down [[Doctor/Legends|Doctor]] [[Maldien]]'s [[Illegal Lab (Corellia)|illegal lab]] on [[Corellia/Legends|Corellia]].<ref name="SWG:CMStD">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=general|Coronet Murmurs: Shut them Down|Corellia}}</ref> A spacer later collected a D-18 Liquidator on [[Vreni Island]].<ref name="SWG:RPWMI">{{SWGcite|exp=NGE|type=collection|Rare Pistol Weapons Mark I}}</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
''[[The Rebel Alliance Sourcebook]]'' and ''[[Arms & Equipment Guide]]'' both feature incorrect images of the DL-18. The correct image is sometimes referred to informally as a "Skiff guard pistol" and can be seen clearly in [[Star Wars: Episode VI Return of the Jedi|''Star Wars'': Episode VI ''Return of the Jedi'']].

